reviews.review: Literally the worst people ever. I had a cargo van with me to unload a bed and bed frame. Keep in mind I LIVE at THE PARAMOUNT. My rent is paying for their salary. I said I will be leaving once I finish bringing the bed upstairs and he said okay but to still give him the keys. I come back down no more than 4 minutes later and the van has been moved and they were demanding me to pay for an hour of parking. Telling me I cant just leave the van parked there. Like are you guys fucking idiots? Did you clearly not see me running up and down to move things in? I wasn't just leaving the van there for fun and games. The stupid dude NEVER TOLD ME IF I STAYED THERE, THEY WILL CHARGE ME. HE JUST ASKED FOR THE KEYS AND GAVE ME SOME BULLSHIT EXCUSE. I argued my way out of it and was able to leave without paying. Literally the worst people. I literally fucking live there.

Horrible experience. After paying at the pay station and immediately walking to my car, we drove down from the fourth floor to the exit on the first. Due to traffic congestion inside the garage, we exceeded the time permitted.

I was only given short responses which were difficult to understand due to the poor audio quality but were instructing me to leave my car to walk to the pay station. reviews.review:
I would leave a negative review if I could. I stayed at the Parc 55 and had my car parked by valet. Upon returning my car, I had a ding in the passenger side door. I reported this immediately to an attendant. I later received a letter from Connecticut stating the ding was pre- existing (which is a highly incorrect statement). I asked for evidence to support this claim. The representative from Propark then emailed me a piece of paper from Propark with a car diagram on it with an X on the passenger side door. The representative stated this was the proof that the ding was pre- existing. Unbelievable! This was not a diagram filled out after a joint inspection by the attendant and myself in which I signed in agreement. This was offered after the fact. When I made the initial complaint at Parc 55, the supervisor took a report and did not even mention this "evidence". This evidence was created after the report was taken I am sure. Before I leave my car with any valet service, I walk around it in order to check the body. I take very good care of my car. Due to the valet service,
My family and I will never stay at this location again. Where is the honorable and just business practice? This whole experience was highly unsavory and dishonest.

They requested another payment because I OVERSTAYED 15 minutes after the payment! I paid for 1 hour, stayed 52 minutes, and was forced to pay for 2 hours. When I told them I did not want to pay twice for the same hour, the guy left me there, with my car locked by the exit, and told me I would not leave without paying. He did not even want to talk and disappeared. Only after I called the police and threatened to block the exit, more than 30 minutes later, a supervisor came to talk to me. He said that I passed my "grace period" after my payment. This does not make ANY sense. A person can stay 1 hour plus 15 minutes for a grace period for $10. However, I stayed 52 minutes and needed to pay twice just because I followed the signs and paid before entering my car instead of paying by the gate. reviews.name: Yaya L.
reviews.review: This was a horrible experience. Turquoise Parking does not honor what they advertise. When I got to the parking lot, I was told it as completely full and that they could not get me a parking space. They said that even if there was a spot available that they would not honor the parking pass because the parking for that day was not $15 dollars that I paid, but $40 dollars and I would have to pay the difference. I told them that I would pay the difference and the lot attendant said no, that there was no parking spaces, I clearly saw one in front. I got there around 7:45 pm, the event started at 8 pm. I assumed that by booking a space using the ParkWhiz app I was guaranteed a parking space. No where in the posting did I see that they would make me pay the difference either.
